The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically paraphrase generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed model is based on the encoder-decoder framework, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The model uses word embeddings, which are a popular technique in natural language processing and machine learning (cs.AI). The model also uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in neural networks for various tasks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on text summarization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
